# Infrastructure Change: <brief description>
#
# Provide a clear, concise summary of the infrastructure change in the first line.
# Use imperative mood: "Add CloudWatch alarms" not "Added CloudWatch alarms"
#
# Example: "Add CloudWatch monitoring to webserver cluster"

## What Changed
# Describe WHAT infrastructure resources are being modified and WHY.
# Focus on business value and operational impact.
#
# Example:
# - Added 4 CloudWatch alarms for CPU and ALB metrics
# - Created SNS topic for alert notifications
# - Deployed CloudWatch dashboard for cluster visibility
# - Improves incident response time by 50%

## Terraform Plan Summary
# REQUIRED: Include resource counts from terraform plan output
# Created: 0 | Modified: 0 | Destroyed: 0
#
# If any resources are destroyed, explain why and confirm approval.

## Blast Radius
# REQUIRED: What breaks if this apply fails halfway through?
# Consider:
# - Which environments are affected?
# - Are there downstream dependencies?
# - Does this touch shared resources (VPC, IAM, security groups)?
# - Will in-flight requests be interrupted?
#
# Example:
# - All changes are additive (no modifications to existing resources)
# - If apply fails after SNS topic creation, orphaned topic can be cleaned up
# - No production traffic affected
# - Rollback: git revert + re-run pipeline

## Testing
# Confirm testing performed:
# - [ ] terraform fmt passed
# - [ ] terraform validate passed
# - [ ] terraform plan reviewed
# - [ ] Unit tests passed (terraform test)
# - [ ] Manual testing in dev environment

## Related
# Link to related tickets, PRs, or documentation
# Closes #<issue-number>
# Related to #<issue-number>
# See: <documentation-url>

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Commit Message Guidelines:
# 
# 1. First line: 50 chars max, imperative mood
# 2. Blank line after first line
# 3. Body: Wrap at 72 characters
# 4. Include plan summary (created/modified/destroyed counts)
# 5. Document blast radius for all changes
# 6. Link to tickets/PRs
# 7. Use conventional commit prefixes:
#    - infra: Infrastructure changes
#    - feat: New features
#    - fix: Bug fixes
#    - docs: Documentation only
#    - test: Test changes
#    - refactor: Code refactoring
#    - chore: Maintenance tasks
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────